Mesosoma (
Fig. 53
) with pronotum weakly sculptured; mesoscutum and scutellum with reticulate sculpture (the cells smaller and less conspicuous on anterior scutellum; on posterior scutellum, the cells in the middle not as elongate as on the sides); metanotum smooth, with posterior margin broadly rounded; propodeum (
Fig. 54
) mostly smooth, with median carina shorter than median areole; lateral carinae subparallel, extending to anterior margin of propodeum.

Distribution. PALAEARCTIC: Austria , Bulgaria ( Donev 1990a [as
O. flaviventris
]), Kyrgyzstan *, Poland *, Romania , Russia *, Sweden *, and Switzerland *.
